Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Kedar Jadhav, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Jadhav has been put out of his misery. Commentary Text: Shami to Williamson, out Bowled!! Now, now! Careful, SRH. PBKS aren't leaving this easy. Shami reaps the rewards for that lovely straight seam of his. Got this length ball out with a slightly wobble seam, the seam dances as it approaches the batter, lands on the pitch and cuts back in. Williamson was looking for a drive away from the body and that shot isn't easy with seam movement on these slow decks. The edge knocks the leg stump out of the groove. It's 10/2. Williamson b Shami 1(6)

Commentary Text: Shami to Warner, out Caught by Rahul!! Edged and taken. A short ball wide outside off stump, Warner will smash those 9 times out of 10 over backward point, but he nicks off to the delight of KL and his his boys. Warner had his feet stuck to the crease and just used his hands to reach out. Interestingly this ball swung away a tad very late to make life difficult for the batter and the edge resulted. This early wicket spices the chase up. Warner c Rahul b Shami 2(3)
